<section id="source-ordering">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="column medium-12">
      <div class="content">
        <h2>Source Ordering</h2>
        <p>Using the source ordering classes you can shift columns around between the breakpoints. For instance, using .medium-push-# you can have a sub-nav on the left for large displays but below for small ones.</p>
        <h4>classes:</h4>
        <p><code>.small-push-#</code>: push the div to the left relative position at the small size</p>
        <p><code>.medium-push-#</code>: push the div to the left relative position at the medium size (inherit value from <code>small</code> if not defined)</p>
        <p><code>.large-push-#</code>: push the div to the left relative position at the large size (inherit value from <code>medium</code> if not defined)</p>
        <p><code>.x-large-push-#</code>: push the div to the left relative position at the x-large size (inherit value from <code>large</code> if not defined)</p>
        <br/>
        <p><code>.small-pull-#</code>: push the div to the right relative position at the small size</p>
        <p><code>.medium-pull-#</code>: push the div to the right relative position at the medium size (inherit value from <code>small</code> if not defined)</p>
        <p><code>.large-pull-#</code>: push the div to the right relative position at the large size (inherit value from <code>medium</code> if not defined)</p>
        <p><code>.x-large-pull-#</code>: push the div to the right relative position at the x-large size (inherit value from <code>large</code> if not defined )</p>
        <br/>
        <p><code>.medium-unpush</code>: cancel the push value from small size</p>
        <p><code>.medium-unpull</code>: cancel the pull value from small size</p>
        <p><code>.large-unpush</code>: cancel the push value from medium size</p>
        <p><code>.large-unpull</code>: cancel the pull value from medium size</p>
        <p><code>.x-large-unpush</code>: cancel the push value from large size</p>
        <p><code>.x-large-unpull</code>: cancel the pull value from large size</p>
        <h4>example:</h4>
    <pre class="prettyprint linenums">
&lt;div class="row"&gt;
  &lt;div class="small-2 medium-push-10 columns"&gt;2&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="small-10 medium-pull-2 columns"&gt;10, last&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="row"&gt;
  &lt;div class="small-4 medium-push-8 large-unpush columns"&gt;4&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="small-8 medium-pull-4 large-unpull columns"&gt;8, last&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
    </pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row example">
    <div class="small-2 medium-push-10 columns">
      <div class="content">
        <p>2</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="small-10 medium-pull-2 columns">
      <div class="content">
        <p>10 last</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row example">
    <div class="small-4 medium-push-8 large-unpush columns">
      <div class="content">
        <p>4</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="small-8 medium-pull-4 large-unpull columns">
      <div class="content">
        <p>8 last</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
